trans-unit.source: Provides a <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> for the title bar of a special group of items in the Explorer Bar.

The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.ExplorerBar.SpecialGroupHead.Normal%2A> property of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.ExplorerBar.SpecialGroupHead> class gets a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> that represents the title bar of a special group of items in the Explorer Bar, such as the **Music Tasks** group in Windows Explorer.
Gets a visual style element that represents the title bar of a special group of items in the Explorer Bar.

You can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> returned by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.ExplorerBar.SpecialGroupHead.Normal%2A> property to create a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleRenderer>.
A <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> that represents the title bar of a special group of items in the Explorer Bar.
